# Trivy ignore file for gitops-demo-app
#
# CVEs listed here are acknowledged, reviewed, and accepted with documented
# justifications. Each entry must include: CVE ID, affected package, reason
# for acceptance, and next review date.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CVE-2026-33671: picomatch ReDoS via crafted extglob patterns
# Package: picomatch (transitive via npm tooling)
# Severity: HIGH
#
# Reason for acceptance:
# picomatch performs glob pattern matching on user-supplied inputs. Our app
# (gitops-demo-app) exposes three endpoints: /, /healthz, and /metrics.
# None of these accept glob patterns, regex, or filesystem path inputs from
# callers. The attack surface for exploiting this ReDoS is therefore zero in
# our context — picomatch is not reachable from any user-controlled input path.
#
# Mitigation plan:
# Next Node.js / npm release cycle may propagate the fixed picomatch
# (>=4.0.4) through the transitive dependency tree automatically. Re-scan
# and remove this entry when that happens.
#
# Next review: 2026-07-23
# Ref: https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-33671
CVE-2026-33671
